process with that, and they were able to link into their initial meeting, and we'd given some advice before just around consent, and different issues around data and support really, and just being really clear about how this affects the person on the ground, that goes into that study really. My post will end in four weeks' time at the ICB, so all clinical safety documentation is clearly labelled, and in a safe accessible place, I'm meeting with the CCIO Rowan Syl for LLR next week, to just have a conversation really, make him aware of current work streams, but this would be my last DDAP meeting I'm afraid, but thanks everyone for your support, and it's been a really helpful role, never two years ago did I believe that I would be in a role as a clinical safety officer, but it's been really helpful and productive, so thanks everyone, and hopefully we'll cross paths in the future. I'm just going to turn off the slides, and just, Colin? I was just going to say, firstly thanks Claire for all the stunning work that you've done, now to put up with all of the contingents, hopefully your life will be easier once you go back into the UHN. Right, two things, one, do we have a timescale yet on the immunology stuff, because it has been bubbling over for what, six months now, eight months? I think it's complete, my understanding is the work is complete, and we're waiting for a final report, I haven't seen that as yet, that would come in to my quality colleagues here as well, and I've kept that open until I've seen that final report. Very good, and the second thing is, have you heard about the latest snafu yet? About the documents, and the fact that there was a problem with practices that had over 14 characters, we've got four practices that are suddenly receiving, in one day, 300-400 documents that have been lost in the system, I just didn't know whether you, I would have thought you should have heard about that, or if KTH and UHN kept it under their hat. Okay, so these are documents coming in from the acute? Yeah, well they were supposed to come in, they found out there was an issue, and suddenly they were arriving, hundreds at a time, into practices which is a reasonably big clinical safety. Yes, yeah. I'm sorry, Kirsty's not on the call, but I understand, when Kirsty went to Morocco, she left me with a lot of paperwork around that, and I was expecting a call from UHN, but I didn't actually receive one, I think they possibly were handling that themselves, so we'll find out, and we'll try to deal with the fallout from whatever happened, with those documents not making it. No, it's just that we've had practices, shall we say, raising this as an issue, and I've raised it with Kirsty, and with Richard Mitchell, etc, and all I get is the standard, oh, we're looking at it, but it doesn't help the GPs on the ground. I'd say one this week had 380 letters appear, suddenly, on one day. Yeah, just thought it should be raised here as well, as it didn't seem to be on the log, thank you. Apologies. About that, I didn't get any more information on that, and obviously, if Kirsty was here, she could probably give you an answer, I'll ask her to respond to that. We're on to any other business, I just wanted to, I probably stole my thunder, but I wanted to thank Claire for everything she's done. I'm sure that all of our team are extremely grateful to the work she's done, not just on End of Life, but as a CSO for us over the last, oh, it's quite a while now, isn't it? How long is it? But we're extremely grateful, and we're glad you're not going too far, hoping that we can maybe, for the young years, find something else in the future. Thank you so much, Claire. Absolutely, thank you. Just to say, we are about to go into our own tuning process as a team, so myself, Katie, Tunde, Adrian, and Steve will all be tuned over to Lecturer Partnership Trust to join the rest of the digital team there. And what isn't going to change is that we're still going to be doing the same thing for all intents and purposes, and working on behalf of the system for our current projects. I guess what will make changes that we might have combined, and do that with less than share in the future, but we've got all that to discuss when we move over in June. So don't hold me to anything yet. Thank you very much, everybody. Anything else for any other business?$RECOVERY$,
